column2: Independent and capable of organizing life autonomously. Potentially self-centered. Strong focus on areas of personal expression and self-development.
Receptive to others and sensitive to relationship undercurrents. Attuned to emotional dynamics and interpersonal nuances.
Approaches relationships with objectivity rather than personal attachment. Seeks public engagement and active participation in society.
Driven to make a significant impact on the world. This motivation can be beneficial but may become disruptive when idealistic pursuits become excessive.
